LAYER 3: CONDITIONAL TRANSFORMATION
how Fadriel sees rules that apply differently to different objects

observe spatial_perception.rana

some puzzles don't apply the same rule to everything
they ask: "IF this shape has property X, THEN do Y, OTHERWISE do Z"
the condition can be size, color, position, shape, or neighbor count

@spatial_rule recolor_by_size
CHECK only colors change, not positions
DETECT clusters of same color but different sizes
LEARN which sizes get recolored and which don't
FIND the size threshold that separates changed from unchanged
VERIFY threshold separates correctly for all pairs
APPLY recolor by size threshold in test
SPEECH "shapes bigger than {threshold} change color"

@spatial_rule recolor_by_neighbor
CHECK only colors change
DETECT which cells changed based on their neighbor context
LEARN the quantum context → new color mapping
VERIFY mapping is consistent
APPLY quantum mapping to test
SPEECH "each cell's new color depends on its neighbors"

@spatial_rule remove_by_isolation
CHECK some shapes vanish (change to background)
DETECT which shapes vanished vs stayed
LEARN the property that distinguished them (isolation, size, coupling)
VERIFY property correctly predicts which vanish
APPLY remove shapes matching the vanish criterion
SPEECH "isolated shapes disappear"

@spatial_rule transform_by_type
CHECK different shapes undergo different transformations
DETECT shape types in input (dots, lines, rects, blobs)
LEARN which transform applies to which type
VERIFY type-specific transforms match output
APPLY type-specific transform to test
SPEECH "dots get stamped, lines get extended, rects get filled"

the key to conditional transformation:
not all objects obey the same rule
the PROPERTY of the object determines the RULE
find the property that splits objects into groups
then find the rule for each group

possible splitting properties:
- size (big vs small)
- color (red vs blue)
- shape (dots vs lines vs rects)
- coupling (isolated vs connected)
- coherence (strong bonds vs weak bonds)
- position (edge vs interior)
- neighbor count (surrounded vs exposed)

@perceive conditional
DETECT changes that are NOT uniform across all shapes
GROUP shapes by which transformation they underwent
FIND the property that separates the groups
LEARN the conditional rule: IF property THEN transform
